        case ESP_MATTER_ATTR_TYPE_UINT8:
            // Handle uint8 attributes
            break;
        default:
            // Handle unknown attribute types
            break;
    }
    return ESP_OK;
}
```
This example demonstrates how the code could be improved by encapsulating related data and functions within a class, using safer alternatives to `strcpy` and `strcat`, and adding comments to explain the purpose of each function. Additionally, it shows how a switch statement could be used to handle different attribute types.
